value.value: A rounded  cartilage lying in the postaxial margin of the mesopodium, adjacent to the distal end of the fibulare.

definition.value: Often consider atavistic when present in extant salamnders (Caudata)

value.value: Either of a pair of cartilaginous rods that support the intromittent organ of male Ascaphus, and are attached to the posteroventral part of the pelvic girdle.
Eversible phalloid portion of the cloaca that is inserted in the female's vent during copulation. Found in male Caecillians.
A tail like posterior extension of the cloaca supported by a pair of Nobelian rods.
Part of the fin consisting of a supporting core of mesenchyme and extracellular matrix.
Part of the fin consisting of flattened epidermal cells elevated into a keel-like structure.

definition.value: In frogs (Anura) the outer fin tissue is present only in tadpoles and sometimes during the embryogenesis of species without tadpoles. In salamanders and caecilians tail fins can persist into reproductive maturity.

value.value: The site of bicarbonate resorption in the adult kidney. It is equivalent to the convoluted distal segment of metanephric nephrons.
The smallest of the blood vessels, parts of the microcirculation, of the liver.

It arises on the lateral epicondyle of the humerus by two heads: the lateral one arises by a thin tendon in common with the m.extensor carpi ulnaris with fibers proximally fused. The internal one arises by a short tendon in common with proximally fused fibers of the m. extensor carpi radialis. It divides distally in two heads: the external head inserts with a long and thin tendon on the metacarpal V, at the same point of insertion of the m. abductor brevis dorsalis digiti V; the internal one inserts by a thin tendon on the proximal region of the metacarpal IV, between the m. extensor brevis superficialis digiti IV and the m. extensor brevis medius digiti IV (Pristimantis bogotensis).
Marginal zone that is a key embryonic tissue region of the early gastrula stage embryo and that houses the Spemann-Mangold organizer.
